ner-badge-1620660658.png";s:5:"thumb";s:123:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQK4b99SWXzaYnwSclrx4dgmuuClUWOns-akfMlg-qrTE3t12ueJW-fB7iKmEOt4kNwO94";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"png";s:5:"width";i:222;s:6:"height";i:445;s:6:"source";s:56:"https://precisiondoormacon.com/garage-door-opener-repair";s:6:"domain";s:22:"precisiondoormacon.com";}i:20;a:11:{s:7:"keyword";s:39:"chamberlain garage door arrows flashing";s:4:"slug";s:39:"chamberlain-garage-door-arrows-flashing";s:5:"title";s:70:"Garage Doors That Won T Close 20 Reasons Your Overhead Door Won T Shut";s:3:"alt";s:70:"garage doors that won t close 20 reasons your overhead door won t shut";s:3:"url";s:87:"http://repair.garagedoorguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/garage-door-wont-close.jpg";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQZ16bUzcLD9d4gjkTQd5NtqkRexu4YH9qHlA";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:651;s:6:"height";i:1200;s:6:"source";s:51:"https://garagedoorguide.com/garage-door-wont-close/";s:6:"domain";s:19:"garagedoorguide.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:56:{i:0;s:65:"Chamberlain Group explains what flashing up and down arrows mean.";i:1;s:66:"Security 20 garage door openers have self-diagnostic capabilities.";i:2;s:130:"The UP and DOWN arrows on the garage door opener flash a diagnostic code then pause before repeating indicating a potential issue.";i:3;s:63:"Garage Door Opener Lights Flash and the Garage Door Wont Close.";i:4;s:148:"When you see your garage door opener lights flashing and the garage door will not close it could be the safety reversing sensors or the LOCK button.";i:5;s:75:"If there is a safety reversing sensor issue the main lights flash 10 times.";i:6;s:39:"Start with aligning the safety sensors.";i:7;s:125:"If you see the up arrow blink only once and the down arrow blink twice it means that your garage door opener would not close.";i:8;s:38:"The main LED light should be flashing.";i:9;s:93:"This happens because the photocell wire has been cut or more possibly the wires are reversed.";i:10;s:147:"Find the Chamberlain garage door opener technical support you need to help fix any issues you may be having with your garage door opener and parts.";i:11;s:113:"From informational videos to product manuals and troubleshooting articles the Chamberlain Group resource library.";i:12;s:45:"Button or wall panel push button is flashing.";i:13;s:123:"The Chamberlain Liftmaster Craftsman garage door opener wall buttons will flash when the opener is placed in lock-out mode.";i:14;s:141:"The garage door opener flashing wall button is completely different from photo-cell LED light being out or the motor head LED light flashing.";i:15;s:88:"The constantly flashing wall button simply means that the door was either put into lock.";i:16;s:76:"Chamberlain garage door openers function the same way as LiftMaster openers.";i:17;s:93:"Any issues regarding flashing lights and diagnosis light codes are the same for both openers.";i:18;s:156:"Other opener brands such as Craftsman and Raynor also use a self-diagnosis LED light indicator with the same light codes as both LiftMaster and Chamberlain.";i:19;s:69:"My garage door opener lights will not turn off when the door is open.";i:20;s:129:"The garage door opener is equipped with a feature that turns the light on when the safety reversing sensors have been obstructed.";i:21;s:52:"This feature can be disabled using the door control.";i:22;s:49:"My neighbors remote control opens my garage door.";i:23;s:199:"If you own a garage door opener by Lift Master Chamberlain or Craftsman youll notice that the sender sensor will usually shine a yellow light and the receiver sensor will usually shine a green light.";i:24;s:136:"If you see that the sender sensor is not yellow and the receiver sensor is not green then this means that your sensors are probably off.";i:25;s:146:"Chamberlain garage door openers with yellow or blue force adjustment dials flash the LED next to the Learn button to indicate a component failure.";i:26;s:208:"To find troubleshooting advice to correct a failure when your Chamberlain garage door opener Learn button is flashing look up the condition causing the flashes and follow the repair advice to fix the problem.";i:27;s:46:"For example 5 flashes indicate that the motor.";i:28;s:85:"8 rows The LED functions as a diagnostic indicator by slowly flashing a failure code.";i:29;s:96:"The garage door opener lights will flash or hear two clicks indicating it has been reprogrammed.";i:30;s:54:"How to connect Chamberlain garage door opener to wifi.";i:31;s:100:"To connect your garage door opener to Wi-Fi and control it with MyQ app you will need the following.";i:32;s:23:"A tablet or smartphone.";i:33;s:37:"A strong Wi-Fi signal in your garage.";i:34;s:130:"There are some instances when your new Chamberlain garage door opener lights keep flashing but the garage door wont close or open.";i:35;s:73:"The problem could lie in the LOCK button or the safety reversing sensors.";i:36;s:63:"Someone must have turned on the LOCK feature on the motor unit.";i:37;s:126:"When you try to access your door using a remote or clicker while the lock system is engaged youll notice that the garage door.";i:38;s:111:"Flashing garage door lights are like a Check Engine Light will indicate which part needs to be addressed fixed.";i:39;s:117:"If that happens contact a garage door specialist as these experts know electric garage door openers like no one else.";i:40;s:95:"On the rear of the motor housing there are indicator arrows one pointing up and the other down.";i:41;s:75:"Count the number times these arrows blink and refer to the following table.";i:42;s:53:"48 Chamberlain Garage Door Opener Arrows Flashing US.";i:43;s:48:"No more flashing arrows on the back of the unit.";i:44;s:105:"No matter how you use your garage theres a chamberlain opener that fits your familys lifestyle and needs.";i:45;s:47:"Chamberlain Garage Door Opener Keypad Flashing.";i:46;s:40:"Posted on J